1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:02,166
now that we have seen our new machinery

2
00:00:02,166 --> 00:00:04,400
let's talk about how we manage power

3
00:00:04,466 --> 00:00:06,566
even though we are connecting a lot of machines

4
00:00:06,566 --> 00:00:07,900
a 4 amps cable is enough

5
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:10,833
because that's the maximum amperage we are producing

6
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:13,633
that power is provided by four steam turbines

7
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:17,900
each one can use slightly more than 1500 steam per second

8
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:22,666
so a potin pipe with a flow speed of 6000 steam per second should be just enough

9
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,100
talking of power flow

10
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:26,900
our cables have a loss of 1 EU per block

11
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:31,233
which means that we are losing voltage for each additional piece of cable we use

12
00:00:31,266 --> 00:00:33,500
this has two main consequences

13
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,833
the first one is a loss of energy

14
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:39,300
the second one is that a single turbin could no longer be enough

15
00:00:39,466 --> 00:00:41,400
but that's more advanced the stuff

16
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:43,033
all of that is just to say that

17
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:47,100
you should try to keep the most power intensive machines close to the generators

18
00:00:47,166 --> 00:00:50,033
to run the heaviest recipes we are using a lot of steam

19
00:00:50,066 --> 00:00:54,833
all of that steam comes from burning random stuff in our expanded railcraft boiler

20
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:57,166
it is now composed of 12 tanks

21
00:00:57,233 --> 00:01:00,166
meaning it can produce 120 steam per tick

22
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,400
2,400 per second

23
00:01:02,466 --> 00:01:04,566
that's less than half of our needs

24
00:01:04,566 --> 00:01:07,600
but since we won't be running constantly at peak consumption

25
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:09,800
we can fix everything with a bigger buffer

26
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:12,433
and once we managed to stock up some steam

27
00:01:12,433 --> 00:01:14,400
we can start using our workshop

28
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:16,200
the first thing we will want to do

29
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,700
is to stock up some of the most used parts

30
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:22,366
starting from copper wire steel plates and thin cables

31
00:01:22,366 --> 00:01:24,800
since we will need lots of those parts

32
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:26,833
we have equipped those machines with hoppers 

33
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:29,166
to do bigger and unsupervised batches

34
00:01:29,433 --> 00:01:31,633
and to avoid overfilling the output chests

35
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:34,600
we keep some of the excess stuff in some drawers close by

36
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,366
now that we stocked up the basic parts

37
00:01:37,366 --> 00:01:39,166
let's craft a batch of circuits

38
00:01:39,466 --> 00:01:41,800
to help us keep track of the missing materials

39
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:44,400
we bookmark recipes ingredients in NEI

40
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:48,100
we do that recursively for all of the stuff we haven't stocked up

41
00:01:48,166 --> 00:01:49,366
such as resistors

42
00:01:49,366 --> 00:01:52,666
which we can now craft in a more efficient way with an assembler

43
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:58,100
there we also notice that we can double our yield by running copper through an arc furnace to anneal it

44
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:02,000
next we can improve our vacuum tube production process

45
00:02:02,033 --> 00:02:04,433
by using molten metal and annealed copper

46
00:02:04,966 --> 00:02:08,100
once we bookmarked all of the main steps we will be doing

47
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,500
we can link those together

48
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:12,066
and apply the batch multiplier we want to achieve

49
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:14,866
now we just have to collect those ingredients

50
00:02:14,866 --> 00:02:16,566
and Mark them off once acquired

51
00:02:17,266 --> 00:02:18,200
and to speed up

52
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,566
we can try to do multiple things at once

53
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:23,500
that's why we also have some duplicated machines

54
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:27,266
and that's how we can now quickly craft a batch of circuits

55
00:02:27,566 --> 00:02:29,633
but before using those for new machinery

56
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:32,466
we should get a better source of fuel for our boiler

57
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:34,300
there are a lot of different fuels

58
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:36,433
with many different ways of production

59
00:02:36,566 --> 00:02:38,600
but for now we can stick with wood

60
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:42,500
so far we have been gathering it by manually chopping down trees

61
00:02:42,633 --> 00:02:44,966

but we want a lower effort solution


62
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,233
we can do that in many different ways

63
00:02:47,233 --> 00:02:50,200
the first one we will see is by using Steve's carts

64
00:02:50,433 --> 00:02:51,700
as the name suggests

65
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:54,400
this involves some highly customizable minecarts

66
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:57,766
which we shall equip with a wood cutter to achieve our objective

67
00:02:58,166 --> 00:03:00,466
assembling this cart will take quite some time

68
00:03:00,466 --> 00:03:03,566
which you can use to prepare a track where it will be working

69
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:06,500
once everything is ready we can place our cart

70
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,333
give it fuel

71
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:10,200
and admire our new automated wood source

72
00:03:10,366 --> 00:03:13,466
at first sight it may looks slow and with low output

73
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,633
but don't be fooled by appearances

74
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:22,433
you can verify that it is indeed slightly better than a flint axe by looking at its internal storage while it does its job

75
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:25,633
it also has more durability than a flint axe

76
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,066
speed aside

77
00:03:27,066 --> 00:03:31,166
what matters is that it will autonomously bring wood to our base

78
00:03:31,466 --> 00:03:33,100
to increase the combustion of this wood

79
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:36,166
we can pass it through an array of coke ovens to make charcoal

80
00:03:36,166 --> 00:03:38,433
which we can then compress into blocks

81
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:43,266
now if you do not like to have a moving car that requires periodic diamond repairs

82
00:03:43,266 --> 00:03:44,700
I have another option for you

83
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:45,900
forestry farms

84
00:03:46,366 --> 00:03:47,966
those run on cheaper materials

85
00:03:47,966 --> 00:03:49,833
but have a lot of moving parts

86
00:03:50,033 --> 00:03:51,800
if you want a zero maintenance system

87
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:54,566
that also has not constant block by block collection

88
00:03:54,566 --> 00:03:56,566
I suggest moving on to ic2 crops

89
00:03:56,566 --> 00:03:59,100
which outscores the other two systems in every way

90
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,866
except for aesthetics

91
00:04:01,066 --> 00:04:05,400
but the real potential of ic2 crops lies in cross breeding and ore berries

92
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:08,633
and here we can see a cultivation of aluminum and gold

93
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,766
from seeds given by the quest book

94
00:04:11,433 --> 00:04:12,400
on a side note

95
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:17,266
the fruit of those berries can be collected from when the plant reaches the third stage of growth

96
00:04:17,566 --> 00:04:21,433
we could get a better yield by waiting for the fourth and last stage of growth

97
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:24,433
but for that the crops need a block of metal underneath

98
00:04:24,433 --> 00:04:26,100
which we cannot afford yet

99
00:04:26,366 --> 00:04:27,400
and the issue is that

100
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:31,033
our crop manager will be waiting for that unreachable stage of growth

101
00:04:31,266 --> 00:04:34,666
that means we will have to manually collect those for now

102
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:38,400
later on we will automate the collection by having a block of metal underneath

103
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:40,400
like we already did with gold

104
00:04:40,566 --> 00:04:43,166
our crop manager also needs a little bit of power

105
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:45,666
and we are feeding it with a super thin cable

106
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:48,000
this is a chip cable which has no loss

107
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,566
meaning we can make it as long as we like

108
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:53,266
the downside is that it can only carry 8 volts

109
00:04:53,266 --> 00:04:54,966
meaning we need a transformer

110
00:04:55,266 --> 00:04:57,833
this transformer will output up to 4 amps

111
00:04:58,066 --> 00:05:01,266
and since our crop manager can probably take at least 2 amps

112
00:05:01,266 --> 00:05:04,600
we could end up burning the thin 1 amp cable

113
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:07,233
to ensure we do not exceed the maximum amperage

114
00:05:07,233 --> 00:05:08,700
we can use cable diodes

115
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:11,200
in this case a ULV Machine Hull

116
00:05:11,766 --> 00:05:16,400
with that we are running this cheap cable at its limit 8 EU per tick

117
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:19,466
which is enough to harvest 40 crops per second

118
00:05:20,066 --> 00:05:23,433
the next thing we should probably try to get is some aluminum ingots

119
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:25,500
both to fully automate our crops

120
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:27,566
and to move on to the next age

121
00:05:27,666 --> 00:05:29,833
this requires an electric blast furnace

122
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:31,433
and the main challenge here is that

123
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:34,433
some people could have issues locating a mica vein

124
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:37,733
one low effort foolproof way to do that is to

125
00:05:37,733 --> 00:05:42,033
first take a walk on some mountains with a ore finder wand looking for pure tin

126
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,900
this will find us a cassiterite vein

127
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:47,866
from which we can take some samples of cassiterite ore

128
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,633
not to be confused with cassiterite sand

129
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:54,400

now that we have cassiterite ore we can easily locate mica


130
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,766
meaning we can build an EBF

131
00:05:57,366 --> 00:06:00,366
and this machine is going to be one more wiring challenge

132
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:04,800
that's because most of its processes will require 120 EU per tick

133
00:06:04,966 --> 00:06:08,500
and even one less will cause the machine to fail and void items

134
00:06:08,766 --> 00:06:09,833
to achieve such power

135
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:12,466
we will need at least 4 amps of low voltage

136
00:06:12,633 --> 00:06:13,966
as we have already seen

137
00:06:13,966 --> 00:06:15,666
the issue is cable power loss

138
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:17,300
and if we are not careful

139
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:19,866
we could easily fail to meet the requirements

140
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:24,400
sometimes that could be just as easy as disconnecting a single cable connection

141
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:29,900
and we must also not forget to use a good enough pipe to feed those turbines

142
00:06:30,033 --> 00:06:30,800
on a side note

143
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:34,766
I often get asked why I always restricted pipe flow direction

144
00:06:34,766 --> 00:06:39,033
and this is one other thing that may change between updates and gregtech versions

145
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:40,833
but from testing it right now

146
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,900
I will say that for a point to point pipe

147
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:45,000
it doesn't really make much of a difference

148
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,566
however if we add some dead end modification

149
00:06:47,566 --> 00:06:49,100
we can start to see some backflow

150
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:51,400
that will slow down the main pipe flow

151
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:55,500
I will say that you should do that just to make the behavior more predictable

152
00:06:56,066 --> 00:06:58,466
now that we have a working EBF and aluminum

153
00:06:58,466 --> 00:07:00,366
we can also get gallium arsenide

154
00:07:00,366 --> 00:07:02,466
in order to make the new type of circuit

155
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,966
thus moving to the MV age

156
00:07:05,533 --> 00:07:07,666
so after getting a circuit assembler

157
00:07:07,666 --> 00:07:09,666
to cut the cost of making more circuits

158
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:11,633
we rushed our first MV machine

159
00:07:11,766 --> 00:07:12,633
an extruder

160
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:15,166
we really want this machine as soon as possible

161
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:18,600
because it will make crafting parts way easier and cheaper

162
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:21,366
next before doing more progress in this tire

163
00:07:21,366 --> 00:07:23,466
we should fix our energy production

164
00:07:23,766 --> 00:07:27,566
we could upgrade our Railcraft boiler or get more solar boilers

165
00:07:27,666 --> 00:07:30,700
but an interesting option is also the bronze boiler

166
00:07:30,866 --> 00:07:33,700
this one can make enough steam to power 3 blast furnaces

167
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:36,500
and reaches working temperature in less than a minute

168
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:38,766
making fuel management easier

169
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,566
with that we can now get into MV tasks

170
00:07:41,633 --> 00:07:42,400
or better yet

171
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:45,833
let's start from automating stuff we could have done in the previous tire

172
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:02,166
现在我们已经看到了新机器

173
00:00:02,166 --> 00:00:04,400
是时候讲讲电力管理的事情了

174
00:00:04,466 --> 00:00:06,566
尽管已经连接了很多机器

175
00:00:06,566 --> 00:00:07,900
但一根4A的线缆便已足够

176
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:10,833
因为这是我们目前的发电上限

177
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:13,633
由四台蒸汽轮机提供

178
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:17,900
其每秒大约消耗1500L蒸汽

179
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:22,666
所以蒸汽流量6000L/s的粗青铜合金已经足够了

180
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,100
说到电力传输

181
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:26,900
我们的电缆每格损失1EU

182
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:31,233
这意味着我们每使用一根额外的电缆就会失去电压

183
00:00:31,266 --> 00:00:33,500
这有两个主要后果

184
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,833
第一个是能量损失

185
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:39,300
第二个是一个涡轮已经不够用了

186
00:00:39,466 --> 00:00:41,400
但那是更进阶的东西

187
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:43,033
总的来说

188
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:47,100
最耗电的机器应该贴近发电机

189
00:00:47,166 --> 00:00:50,033
为了运行最耗电的配方，我们使用了大量的蒸汽

190
00:00:50,066 --> 00:00:54,833
所有的蒸汽都来自于RC锅炉燃烧掉的随机可燃物

191
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:57,166
它现在有12台储罐

192
00:00:57,233 --> 00:01:00,166
这意味着它每tick可以生产120L蒸汽

193
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,400
2400L每秒

194
00:01:02,466 --> 00:01:04,566
这还不到我们需求的一半

195
00:01:04,566 --> 00:01:07,600
不过我们可不会一直处于消耗巅峰

196
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:09,800
我们可以用更大的缓冲来解决所有问题

197
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:12,433
一旦我们设法储备了一些蒸汽

198
00:01:12,433 --> 00:01:14,400
我们可以开始使用我们的车间

199
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:16,200
我们要做的第一件事

200
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,700
就是储备一些最常用的零件

201
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:22,366
从铜线缆、钢板和细电缆开始

202
00:01:22,366 --> 00:01:24,800
因为我们会大量需要这些零件

203
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:26,833
我们已经为那些机器配备了漏斗

204
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:29,166
用来完成更大批量的被动生产

205
00:01:29,433 --> 00:01:31,633
同时为了避免输出箱被填满

206
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:34,600
我们把多余的东西放在附近的抽屉里

207
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,366
现在我们储备了基本零件

208
00:01:37,366 --> 00:01:39,166
让我们制作一批电路

209
00:01:39,466 --> 00:01:41,800
要让我们能追踪缺少的材料

210
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:44,400
我们在NEI中为配方增加合成链

211
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:48,100
我们对所有没有储备的东西都递归地这样做

212
00:01:48,166 --> 00:01:52,700
比如我们现在可以用组装机来增产的电阻

213
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:58,100
我们还注意到，通过将铜放入电弧炉退火
我们可以将电阻的产出翻倍

214
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:04,433
接下来我们可以通过使用熔融金属和
退火铜来改进真空管生产工艺

215
00:02:04,966 --> 00:02:08,100
一旦我们将要做的所有主要步骤都标记

216
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,500
我们可以把它们联在一起

217
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:12,066
并施加我们想要实现的批乘数

218
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:14,866
现在我们只需要收集那些原料

219
00:02:14,866 --> 00:02:16,566
获得之后就把它们取消标记

220
00:02:17,266 --> 00:02:18,200
而为了加快速度

221
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,566
可以尝试同时做多件事

222
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:23,500
这就是为什么我们也有一些相同的机器

223
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:27,266
这就是我们现在快速制作一组电路的方法

224
00:02:27,566 --> 00:02:29,633
但在将它们用于新机器之前

225
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:32,466
我们应该为锅炉找到更好的燃料来源

226
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:34,300
燃料很多

227
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:36,433
也有很多不同的产出方法

228
00:02:36,566 --> 00:02:38,600
但现在可以继续使用木头

229
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:42,500
到目前为止，我们一直通过手工来砍伐

230
00:02:42,633 --> 00:02:44,966
但我们想要一个麻烦更少的方案

231
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,233
有许多方法

232
00:02:47,233 --> 00:02:50,200
第一个是通过使用史蒂夫矿车模组

233
00:02:50,433 --> 00:02:51,700
顾名思义

234
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:54,400
这涉及到一些高度可定制的矿车

235
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:57,766

我们将为它配备一个伐木器来实现我们的目标


236
00:02:58,166 --> 00:03:00,466
组装这辆车需要相当长的时间

237
00:03:00,466 --> 00:03:03,566
我们利用这段时间在它工作的地方铺设好轨道

238
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:06,500
一旦一切准备就绪，我们就可以放置矿车了

239
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:10,200
加入燃料，欣赏我们新的自动化木材来源

240
00:03:10,366 --> 00:03:13,466
乍一看，它可能看起来很慢，输出也很低

241
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,633
但不要被外表所迷惑

242
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:22,433
你可以通过查看它的内部存储来验证
它确实比燧石斧稍微好一点

243
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:25,633
它也比燧石斧更耐用

244
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:31,166
抛开速度不谈，重要的是
它会自动把木头带到我们的基地

245
00:03:31,466 --> 00:03:33,100
想增加木头的燃烧时间

246
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:36,166
可以让它通过焦炉来制造木炭

247
00:03:36,166 --> 00:03:38,433
然后我们可以将其压缩成块

248
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:43,266
现在如果你不喜欢拥有一个
需要定期使用钻石维修的矿车

249
00:03:43,266 --> 00:03:44,700
这有另一个选择

250
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:45,900
林场

251
00:03:46,366 --> 00:03:47,966
它使用更便宜的材料

252
00:03:47,966 --> 00:03:49,833
但有很多活动部件

253
00:03:50,033 --> 00:03:51,800
如果你想要一个零维护系统

254
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:54,566
也无需具体的方块收集

255
00:03:54,566 --> 00:03:56,566
我建议转向ic2作物

256
00:03:56,566 --> 00:03:59,100
它在各个方面都胜过其他两个系统

257
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,866
除了美学

258
00:04:01,066 --> 00:04:05,400
但ic2作物的真正潜力在于杂交育种和矿石浆果

259
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:10,766
这里我们可以看到由任务书
赠送的种子种下的铝和金矿莓

260
00:04:11,433 --> 00:04:12,400
顺便说一句

261
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:17,266
这些矿莓的果实可以从植物生长到第三阶段时收集

262
00:04:17,566 --> 00:04:21,433
也可以等待其到第四阶段来获得更多产物

263
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:24,433
但庄稼下面需要放一个金属块才能进入那一阶段

264
00:04:24,433 --> 00:04:26,100
我们还负担不起那些

265
00:04:26,366 --> 00:04:31,033
问题是我们的作物管理器
会等待那个遥不可及的生长阶段到来

266
00:04:31,266 --> 00:04:34,666
这意味着我们现在必须手动收集这些

267
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:38,400
稍后，我们将通过在下面放一块金属来自动收集

268
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:40,400
就像我们已经对黄金做的那样

269
00:04:40,566 --> 00:04:43,166
我们的作物管理器也需要一点电

270
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:45,666
我们用一根超细电缆供电

271
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:48,000
这是一根很便宜的超导线缆

272
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,566
意思是我们想搞多长就多长

273
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:53,266
缺点是它最大电压只有8V

274
00:04:53,266 --> 00:04:54,966
这意味着我们需要一个变压器

275
00:04:55,266 --> 00:04:57,833
该变压器将输出高达4A的电流

276
00:04:58,066 --> 00:05:01,266
由于我们的作物管理器可能至少需要2A

277
00:05:01,266 --> 00:05:04,600
这种细线缆可能会被烧了

278
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:07,233
为了确保我们不超过最大电流

279
00:05:07,233 --> 00:05:08,700
我们可以使用电缆二极管

280
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:11,200
在这种情况下，是ULV机器外壳

281
00:05:11,766 --> 00:05:16,400
有了它，其最大功率便被限制在8EU/t

282
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:19,466
这足以每秒收获40株作物

283
00:05:20,066 --> 00:05:23,433
接下来我们可能应该尝试购买一些铝锭

284
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:25,500
都是为了让我们的作物完全自动化

285
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:27,566
为进入下一个时代

286
00:05:27,666 --> 00:05:29,833
这需要一个电高炉

287
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:31,433
这里的主要挑战是

288
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:34,433
有些人可能在定位云母矿脉时遇到问题

289
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:37,733
一个不需要努力且万无一失的方法是

290
00:05:37,733 --> 00:05:42,033
首先带着找寻矿魔杖在山上寻找纯锡

291
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,900
这能找到锡石矿脉

292
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:47,866
我们可以从中提取一些锡石矿石样本

293
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,633
不要与锡石砂混淆

294
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:54,400
而有了锡，云母矿脉便不在话下

295
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,766
这意味着我们可以做一个EBF

296
00:05:57,366 --> 00:06:00,366
这台机器将是另一个布线挑战

297
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:04,800
这是因为它的大部分配方都需要120EU/t

298
00:06:04,966 --> 00:06:08,500
即使少一点也会导致机器故障并使物品被吞

299
00:06:08,766 --> 00:06:12,466
要达到这样的功率，至少要4A的LV电

300
00:06:12,633 --> 00:06:13,966
正如我们已经看到的

301
00:06:13,966 --> 00:06:15,666
问题是线损

302
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:17,300
如果我们不小心

303
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:19,866
很容易达不到要求

304
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:24,400
有时这可能就像断开单个电缆连接一样简单

305
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:29,900
我们也不能忘记使用足够好的管道来为涡轮机供电

306
00:06:30,033 --> 00:06:30,800
顺便说一句

307
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:34,766
我经常被问到为什么我总是限制管道流动方向

308
00:06:34,766 --> 00:06:39,033
这是另一件可能在不同更新
或不同GT版本之间发生变化的事

309
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:40,833
但从现在的测试来看

310
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,900
我会说点对点管道

311
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:45,000
这没什么区别

312
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,566
但是如果我们添加一些死胡同

313
00:06:47,566 --> 00:06:49,100
我们可以看到一些倒流

314
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:51,400
这将降低主管道的流量

315
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:55,500
我会说为了让流动更可预测，你应该这么做

316
00:06:56,066 --> 00:06:58,466
现在我们有一个正常工作的EBF和铝

317
00:06:58,466 --> 00:07:00,366
我们还能弄到砷化镓

318
00:07:00,366 --> 00:07:02,466
用来制造新型电路

319
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,966
从而进入MV时代

320
00:07:05,533 --> 00:07:09,666
所以在拿到能降低制造更多
电路板成本的电路组装机后

321
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:12,633
我们速通出第一台MV机器——压模机

322
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:15,166
这台机器真的越早出越好

323
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:18,600
因为这将使制作零件变得更容易、更便宜

324
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:21,366
在这个阶段取得更多进展前

325
00:07:21,366 --> 00:07:23,466
我们应该修复能源生产

326
00:07:23,766 --> 00:07:27,566
我们可以升级RC锅炉或制作更多太阳能锅炉

327
00:07:27,666 --> 00:07:30,700
但另一个有趣的选择是青铜锅炉

328
00:07:30,866 --> 00:07:33,700
这个可以产生足够的蒸汽来驱动3个高炉

329
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:36,500
并在一分钟内达到工作温度

330
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:38,766
而使燃料管理变得轻松

331
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,566
有了它，我们现在可以进入MV任务

332
00:07:41,633 --> 00:07:42,400
或者最好先不进入

333
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:45,833

让我们先从上一电压本就可以做的自动化开始吧


